  "prompt": "What universities does Federal Signal recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Federal Signal Corporation, a manufacturer of safety, security, and environmental products, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, often targeting institutions with strong engineering, business, and technology programs. While specific universities may vary depending on the year and recruitment needs, they generally look for candidates from well-regarded schools with relevant programs.\n\n### Universities Federal Signal May Recruit From:\n1. **Engineering-focused universities**:  \n   - **Illinois Institute of Technology (IIT)**  \n   - **Purdue University**  \n   - **University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign (UIUC)**  \n   - **Michigan Technological University**  \n   - **University of Michigan**  \n   - **Georgia Institute of Technology**  \n   - **University of Wisconsin-Madison**  \n   - **Ohio State University**  \n   - **Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology**  \n\n2. **Business and technology-focused universities**:  \n   - **University of Chicago**  \n   - **Northwestern University**  \n   - **Indiana University (Kelley School of Business)**  \n   - **Marquette University**  \n   - **University of Notre Dame**  \n\n### Majors Federal Signal Typically Looks For:\n1. **Engineering**:  \n   - Mechanical Engineering  \n   - Electrical Engineering  \n   - Industrial Engineering  \n   - Manufacturing Engineering  \n   - Civil Engineering (for environmental products)  \n   - Software Engineering  \n\n2. **Business and Management**:  \n   - Business Administration  \n   - Supply Chain Management  \n   - Marketing  \n   - Finance  \n\n3. **Technology and IT**:  \n   - Computer Science  \n   - Information Technology  \n   - Data Analytics  \n\n4. **Environmental and Safety Sciences**:  \n   - Environmental Engineering  \n   - Occupational Safety and Health  \n\nFederal Signal often participates in career fairs, on-campus recruiting events, and partnerships with university career centers to identify and attract talented graduates. If you're interested in working with Federal Signal, check with your university's career services office or the company's careers page for specific opportunities and requirements.",
